cs.DC, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on evaluating the efficacy and performance of distributed stream processing systems (DSPS) for IoT applications, which involves processing large amounts of data in real-time. This falls under the scope of distributed computing.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions two IoT applications for statistical summarization and predictive analytics, which involve processing and analyzing data to extract insights. This falls under the scope of information retrieval.
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper discusses the use of DSPS for managing and processing data streams from IoT sensors, which involves storing and retrieving data from databases.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of IoT sensors to monitor physical, environmental, and human systems in real-time, which involves networking and internet architecture.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the development of a benchmark suite and performance metrics to evaluate DSPS for streaming IoT applications, which involves software engineering principles.
